  "text": "The reason why C. parapsilosis and C. guilliermondii isolates with higher CAS MICs responded in vivo to this drug as well as isolates with lower MICs did can be explained with data reported by Louie et al. [CITATION_1] . They found that CAS levels persisted in kidney tissue well after serum concentrations fall below the MIC and thus exerted a greater effect than might be expected.",
